dpkg tool
---------
debian package tool

.deb
-----
man 5 deb 
The .deb format is the Debian binary package file format. It is understood since dpkg 0.93.76, and is generated by default since dpkg 1.2.0 and 1.1.1elf (i386/ELF builds).


environment
------------
$ mkdir -p ~/build-deb/try/debian
$ cd ~/build-deb
$ vi try/DEBIAN/control
Package: try
Version: 0.1
Architecture: all
Description: This is a test package.
Maintainer: developer <jedy.wei@advantech.com.tw>

NOTE:  debian version scheme
        [epoch:]upstrem_version[-debian_revision] 
        2.2.6-1

       architecture : amd64

$ cat /var/lib/dpkg/available   to get a control file example 

build and command
------------------
dpkg or dpkg-deb command

$ dpkg --build try          // -b

$ dpkg --info try.deb       // -I

$ dpkg --field try.deb      // -f

$ dpkg --contents try.deb   // -c



test 
----
$ dpkg -b vegahd_0.9-1_amd64        // --build
$ dpkg -I vegahd_0.9-1_amd64.deb    // --info
$ dpkg -f vegahd_0.9-1_amd64.deb    // --field
$ dpkg -c vegahd_0.9-1_amd64.deb    // --contents

$ sudo dpkg -i vegahd_0.9-1_amd64.deb          // --install
$ sudo apt -f install 
$ dpkg -l vegahd                    // --list
$ dpkg -s vegahd                    // --status
$ dpkg -L vegahd                    // --listfiles 
$ sudo dpkg -r vegahd               // --remove


$ sudo apt install ./vegahd_0.9-1_amd64.deb
$ sudo apt install --reinstall ./vegahd_0.9-1_amd64.deb

fixup
-----
$ sudo dpkg --configure -a
$ sudo apt -f install
$ ls /var/lib/dpkg/info/vegahd.postinst 
$ ls /var/lib/dpkg/info/vegahd.postrm
$ sudo rm /var/lib/dpkg/info/vegahd.post{inst,rm}

packages
- build-essential
- devscripts            // sudo apt install devscripts
- dh_make               // sudo apt install dh-make
- bzr-builddeb          // sudo apt install bzr-builddeb

.dsc    - source package
.deb    - binary package

